headlines.description: — The Buffalo Bills crashed Detroit's Thanksgiving party, making themselves at home for their second victory in five days at Ford Field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills beat Lions 28-25 for 2nd win in 5 days at Ford Field

events.name: New York Giants at Dallas Cowboys

headlines.description: — CeeDee Lamb could only smile when officials upheld an out-of-bounds call on what the Dallas receiver hoped would be a touchdown on his second one-handed catch of the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamb sets table on Thanksgiving as Cowboys beat Giants 28-20

events.name: New England Patriots at Minnesota Vikings

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Vikings have quickly become a confident and resilient team under rookie coach Kevin O'Connell and his staff, and they sure showed it in this short week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cousins, Vikings rebound from blowout to beat Patriots 33-26

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Cleveland Browns

headlines.description: — Jacoby Brissett wasn't seeking sympathy and he didn't want any ceremonial sendoff.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chubb's TD in OT gives Brissett, Browns 23-17 win over Bucs

headlines.description: — The Cincinnati Bengals have a knack for beating the Tennessee Titans at their own game — by playing more physically and forcing the opponent into mistakes at the wrong time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burrow's TD pass to Higgins lifts Bengals over Titans 20-16

headlines.description: — Tua Tagovailoa expressed mild concern this week about not wanting the Miami Dolphins’ bye to interrupt the momentum they had built during a recent winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tagovailoa, Dolphins rout Texans 30-15 for 5th straight win

events.name: Chicago Bears at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Mike White was more than just all right for the New York Jets.
headlines.shortLinkText: White throws 3 TD passes to lead Jets past Bears 31-10

headlines.description: — After running all over the Atlanta Falcons in what has become their
headlines.shortLinkText: Commanders outrun Falcons, intercept Mariota in 19-13 win

headlines.description: — Sam Darnold has been waiting more than 10 months for another chance to prove he can lead the Carolina Panthers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darnold leads Panthers past reeling Broncos 23-10

headlines.description: — Marvin Jones' shin-dragging touchdown catch will go down as one of the more memorable plays in Jacksonville Jaguars history. Zay Jones'
headlines.shortLinkText: Jags edge Ravens 28-27 on 2-pointer, Tucker's 67-yard miss

events.name: Los Angeles Chargers at Arizona Cardinals

headlines.description: — Los Angeles Chargers coach Brandon Staley knew he was going for the winning 2-point conversion a few minutes before it actually happened, so when the moment arrived, there was no hesitation and no looking at his playbook.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herbert rallies Chargers to 25-24 win over Cardinals

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at Seattle Seahawks

headlines.description: — Once Josh Jacobs slipped past the last line of Seattle's defense, all that was in front of him was open field and a place among the greatest single-game performances in NFL history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacobs caps huge day with TD in OT, Raiders beat Seahawks

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — Andy Reid lamented more problems with the Kansas City Chiefs punt return unit. JuJu Smith-Schuster regretted their many failures in the red zone. Patrick Mahomes bemoaned “the one dumb play I make every game."
headlines.shortLinkText: Chiefs slog their way past beat-up Rams for 26-10 victory

events.name: New Orleans Saints at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: — Three straight second-half shutouts were impressive for the San Francisco 49ers. Their prideful defense knew they were capable of even more.
headlines.shortLinkText: 49ers top Saints 13-0, first to blank New Orleans since 2001

events.name: Green Bay Packers at Philadelphia Eagles

headlines.description: — Jalen Hurts ran and ran and he ran so much that Green Bay couldn't catch him as he raced his way into Philadelphia's record book. Hurts outran the Packers and he eclipsed all the other fleet-footed Pro Bowl quarterbacks in Eagles' history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hurts, Eagles run past Packers 40-33; Rodgers hurt

headlines.description: — Benny Snell Jr. kept waiting for his first carry of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Snell runs for go-ahead TD, Steelers hold off Colts 24-17
